content:
Recently I picked up a $100 Lenovo ThinkCentre M710Q with an i5 7400T, 8GB of ram and 256 SSD as a secondary node for hosting monitoring services and smaller applications.
Why they&rsquo;re great Mini PCs are built to be small quiet and efficient, perfect for a home server. Businesses buy them in bulk and then decommision them in bulk for cheap.
Where to buy them I&rsquo;d recommend having a browse on eBay, find a listing with many available and make sure its not &ldquo;barebones&rdquo;

